Prparation des batchs

Nous allons sparer en petites parties le jeu de donne avec tfdatasets. Cela permet de former le modle plus facilement.

df_to_dataset <- function(df, shuffle = TRUE, batch_size = 1024) {
  ds <- df %>% 
    tensor_slices_dataset()
  
  if (shuffle)
    ds <- ds %>% dataset_shuffle(buffer_size = nrow(df))
  
  ds %>% 
    dataset_batch(batch_size = batch_size)
}



batch_size <- 1024
train_ds <- df_to_dataset(train, batch_size = batch_size)
## Loaded Tensorflow version 2.8.0
val_ds <- df_to_dataset(val, shuffle = FALSE, batch_size = batch_size)
test_ds <- df_to_dataset(test, shuffle = FALSE, batch_size = batch_size)

Nous souhaitons prdire la variable churner

spec <- feature_spec(train_ds, churner ~ .)
spec_prep <- spec



Nos variables sont toutes numriques, on choisit de les normalis.

spec <- spec %>%
  step_numeric_column(
    all_numeric()
  )
 spec_prep <- fit(spec)
 str(spec_prep$dense_features())

Cration du modle de Deep-Learning



Cration du modle

model <- keras_model_sequential() %>% 
  layer_dense_features(dense_features(spec_prep)) %>% 
  layer_dense(units = 200, activation = "relu") %>% 
  layer_dropout(0.5) %>%
  layer_dense(units = 100, activation = "relu") %>% 
  layer_dropout(0.4) %>%
  layer_dense(units = 100, activation = "relu") %>% 
  layer_dropout(0.3) %>%
  layer_dense(units = 100, activation = "relu") %>% 
  layer_dropout(0.2) %>%
  layer_dense(units = 1, activation = 'sigmoid')


model %>% compile(
  loss = loss_binary_crossentropy, 
  optimizer = "adam", 
  metrics = "binary_accuracy"
)



Entrainement du modle sur le jeu dentranement

history <- model %>% 
  fit(
    dataset_use_spec(train_ds, spec = spec_prep),
    epochs = 100, 
    validation_data = dataset_use_spec(val_ds, spec_prep),
    verbose = 2
  )

Visualisation des rsultats



Affichage graphique des amliorations de lentranement

plot(history)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'



Prdiction sur le jeu de test.

#prdiction
pred <- predict(model, test)
test$prediction <- pred
predictions = matrix(FALSE, nr = nrow(test), nc = 1)

for (i in 1:nrow(test)) {
  if (test[i, 26] > 0.5) {
    test[i, 26] = TRUE
  }
  else {
    test[i, 26] = FALSE
  }
}
